|access-date=2019-11-17}}</ref>\n|-\n|Bulgy the Whale\n|West Coast Amusements (Showman)\n|\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://westcoastamusements.com/bulgy-the-whale/|title=Bulgy the Whale|website=West Coast Amusements|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-12-18}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{N/A|Unknown}}\n|[[Joyland Amusement Park (Wichita, Kansas)|Joyland Amusement Park]]\n|\n|{{no|Closed}}\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.flatrides.com/rides/bulgythewhale.html|title=Eyerly Bulgy the Whale|website=The Flat Joint|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-12-18}}</ref>\n|-\n|Dancer's Fish\n|[[Holiday World & Splashin' Safari]]\n|\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|Formerly called ''Salmon Run''. Relocated for 2014 season.\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.holidayworld.com/rides/dancers-fish/|title=Dancer's Fish|website=Holiday World|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-12-18}}</ref>\n|}\n\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n\n\n[[Category:Amusement rides]]\n", "text_old": "'''Bulgy the Whale''' is a children's amusement ride manufactured by [[Eyerly Aircraft Company]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.flatrides.com/rides/bulgythewhale.html|title=Eyerly Bulgy the Whale|website=www.flatrides.com|access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref> It consists of eight whale-shaped ride vehicles traveling in a counter-clockwise rotation, similar to a [[carousel]], while traveling up and down small hills. Although the Eyerly Aircraft Company ceased operation in the 1980s, there are still several Bulgy the Whale rides in operation. Some have had their whales repainted to resemble fish instead of whales, and others have had thematic pieces added, but the general operation and idea remains the same.\n\n== Bulgy the Whale Installations ==\nBelow is a partial list of Bulgy the Whale attractions.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Name\n!Park\n!Open\n!Closed\n!Details\n!Ref\n|-\n|Bulgy the Whale\n|[[Lagoon (amusement park)|Lagoon]]\n|1956\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lagoonpark.com/ride/bulgy/|title=Bulgy {{!}} Lagoon|w